  <title translate="true">RowCenter</title>
  <keywords>
    <keyword translate="true">RowCenter</keyword>
  </keywords>
  <body>
    <header>
      <para styleclass="Heading1"><text styleclass="Heading1" translate="true">RowCenter</text></para>
    </header>
    <para styleclass="Normal"><text styleclass="Normal" translate="true">For MODFLOW and PHAST models, </text><text styleclass="Normal" style="font-weight:bold;" translate="true">RowCenter</text><text styleclass="Normal" translate="true">({Row}) returns the Y coordinate in the grid coordinate system of the center of the cell (MODFLOW) or element (PHAST) specified by its one optional argument Row. For SUTRA models, </text><text styleclass="Normal" style="font-weight:bold;" translate="true">RowCenter</text><text styleclass="Normal" translate="true"> returns zero. If the optional argument is not included, the function uses the row number of the cell or element for which the formula is being calculated. &#160;If an invalid row number is specified, </text><text styleclass="Normal" style="font-weight:bold;" translate="true">RowCenter</text><text styleclass="Normal" translate="true"> returns 0.</text></para>
  </body>
